    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.7.2\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nUbuntu 22.04\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nGnome-terminal\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n- run sudo cpanm -n Neovim::Ext\r\n- enter neovim with nvim --clean and run :checkhealth\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nPerl-provider has no problems\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nThe following error is printed:\r\n  - ERROR: Command error (job=18, exit code 2): `/usr/bin/perl '-MApp::cpanminus::fatscript' -e 'my $app = App::cpanminus::script->new; $app->parse_options (\"--info\", \"-q\", \"Neovim::Ext\"); exit $app->doit'` (in \\<my home directory\\>)\r\n    stderr: Can't locate App/cpanminus/fatscript.pm in @INC (you may need to install the App::cpanminus::fatscript module) (@INC contains: /etc/perl /usr/local/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/perl/5.34.0 /usr/local/share/perl/5.34.0 /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/perl5/5.34 /usr/share/perl5 /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/perl-base /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/perl/5.34 /usr/share/perl/5.34 /usr/local/lib/site_perl).BEGIN failed--compilation aborted.\r\n  - ERROR: Failed to run: /usr/bin/perl -MApp::cpanminus::fatscript -e my $app = App::cpanminus::script->new; $app->parse_options (\"--info\", \"-q\", \"Neovim::Ext\"); exit $app->doit\r\n\r\nThanks in advance for any help!",
